When editing Confluence pages in Chrome (presumably other unsupported browsers as well) the rich text editor is not accessible. This is fine, except there is no indication of why the rich text editor is not accessible. It took several minutes of confusion, trying to see if I'd somehow disabled the editor, before it occurred to me to try in Firefox.

I suggest adding some sort of indication when editing to indicate the rich text editor has been disabled because it is not compatible with the current browser.

